# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# UnstableStonks configuration. Everything works out of the box against public
# endpoints — these vars only OVERRIDE defaults or unlock optional features.
# Copy to `.env` and fill in what you need. Client vars must be prefixed VITE_.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── RPC overrides (default to each network's public RPC) ────────────────────
# VITE_RPC_ROBINHOOD=https://rpc.mainnet.chain.robinhood.com
# VITE_RPC_STABLE=https://rpc.stable.xyz
# VITE_RPC_ARC=https://rpc.testnet.arc.network

# ── Block-explorer v2 API bases (default to each chain's Blockscout) ─────────
# Stable's public explorer (stablescan.xyz) is Etherscan-powered; the token/stat
# feeds use its Blockscout instance instead. Override if the host differs.
# VITE_EXPLORER_API_STABLE=https://blockscout.stable.xyz/api/v2
# VITE_EXPLORER_API_ARC=https://testnet.arcscan.app/api/v2

# ── DEX price indexers (GeckoTerminal network slug per chain) ────────────────
# Robinhood is wired ("robinhood"); Stable defaults to "stable". DYORswap (Stable's
# DEX) is indexed by GeckoTerminal, so pools populate the table once the slug is
# right — override here if GeckoTerminal lists Stable under a different slug.
# VITE_GT_NETWORK_STABLE=stable

# ── Swap routing + fee collection ────────────────────────────────────────────
# The 1% treasury fee (-> 0x6E53C6288Dc2C0F957Dc1F5E7d78874c3223CC96) works on any
# chain via a plain transfer. The DEX swap leg activates per chain once you set a
# router address (+ wrapped-native where not defaulted). Both Uniswap V2- and
# V3-style routers are supported:
#   VITE_ROUTER_<CHAIN>       router address (V2Router02 or SwapRouter02)
#   VITE_ROUTER_KIND_<CHAIN>  "v2" (default) | "v3"
#   VITE_QUOTER_<CHAIN>       QuoterV2 address — required when kind is v3
#   VITE_FEE_TIER_<CHAIN>     v3 fee tier, default 3000 (0.3%)
# Robinhood + Arc ship with VERIFIED Uniswap V3 addresses baked in (from Uniswap's
# official SDK) — no env needed. Robinhood buys/sells work out of the box.
# Override only if you want a different router:
# VITE_ROUTER_ROBINHOOD=0x...  VITE_ROUTER_KIND_ROBINHOOD=v3  VITE_QUOTER_ROBINHOOD=0x...  VITE_WNATIVE_ROBINHOOD=0x...
#
# Stable's Uniswap V3 addresses aren't in the SDK yet. Grab SwapRouter02 + QuoterV2
# + wrapped USDT0 from docs.stable.xyz/en/reference/dexes (or DYORswap, its V2 DEX)
# and set them here to enable Stable swaps + the 1% fee:
# VITE_ROUTER_STABLE=0x...        # Stable SwapRouter02 (v3) or DYORswap router (v2)
# VITE_ROUTER_KIND_STABLE=v3     # v3 for Uniswap, v2 for DYORswap
# VITE_QUOTER_STABLE=0x...        # QuoterV2 (v3 only)
# VITE_WNATIVE_STABLE=0x...       # wrapped USDT0 (WUSDT0)
# VITE_WNATIVE_STABLE=0x...       # wrapped USDT0 (WUSDT0)
# VITE_ROUTER_ARC=0x...
# VITE_WNATIVE_ARC=0x...

# ── X (Twitter) social crawl (server-side secrets, NOT VITE_) ────────────────
# Preferred: official X API v2 bearer token — authoritative posts + impressions.
# X_BEARER_TOKEN=
# Fallback: comma-separated Nitter instances used when no bearer token is set.
# X_NITTER_INSTANCES=https://nitter.net,https://nitter.poast.org
